******
[3] Sierra Leone: more UK volunteers
Date: Sat 22 Nov 2014
Source: Daily Mail [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2844893/NHS-staff-head-Ebola-mission.html


1st group of NHS volunteers fly out from Heathrow to tackle Ebola crisis in Sierra Leone
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NHS [National Health Service] staff join the fight against Ebola: 30 GPs [general practitioners], nurses and psychiatrists fly to Sierra Leone in 1st wave of volunteers deployed by the government. More than 1000 NHS staff have volunteered to travel to fight Ebola. The 1st group of 30 doctors and nurses will fly out later today [22 Nov 2014]. The British team will undergo a final week's training in Sierra Leone. Already, 1000 British personnel are in the field building new clinics.... -- more

[Byline: Darren Boyle]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[5 NHS workers from Scotland are part of a UK team of medical volunteers heading to Sierra Leone to help in the fight against Ebola, and an intensive care registrar at Ysbyty Gwynedd in Bangor [Wales, UK], will join them (BBC). - Mod.JW]

